        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:44PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Alva, or 19 miles north of Sundance, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alva and Bear Lodge Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
